00:56:36,749 --> 00:56:38,282
♪ Turn on The Juice ♪

826
00:56:38,284 --> 00:56:39,450
♪ Yeah ♪

827
00:56:39,452 --> 00:56:40,985
I didn't wanna miss any of it.

828
00:56:40,987 --> 00:56:44,421
♪ Turn on The Juice ♪

829
00:56:44,423 --> 00:56:47,791
It was the most exciting
thing that I'd ever seen.

830
00:56:47,793 --> 00:56:50,427
♪ Turn on The Juice ♪

831
00:56:50,429 --> 00:56:51,996
♪ Yeah ♪

832
00:57:05,811 --> 00:57:09,513
When we got to New York, that last game,

833
00:57:09,515 --> 00:57:11,315
he was going for Jim Brown's record.

834
00:57:13,419 --> 00:57:17,187
With 60 yards needed, and everyone knew

835
00:57:17,189 --> 00:57:22,159
that The Jets didn't want
him to get the record.

836
00:57:22,161 --> 00:57:27,998
I was actually there. The Jets had
no chance of making the playoffs.

837
00:57:28,000 --> 00:57:30,134
The only interesting thing about that day

838
00:57:30,136 --> 00:57:32,569
was whether O.J. was going to break 2,000.

839
00:57:34,874 --> 00:57:38,509
It was a really snowy, cold day.

840
00:57:38,511 --> 00:57:41,178
Hm, a little bit similar to today.

841
00:57:41,180 --> 00:57:42,479
So a lot of people were worried

842
00:57:42,481 --> 00:57:44,114
that he wouldn't have
a lot of rushing yards

843
00:57:44,116 --> 00:57:47,651
because of that, a lot
of slipping in the snow.

844
00:57:47,653 --> 00:57:50,120
He was nervous that day.

845
00:57:50,122 --> 00:57:53,057
We had a little chat,
and I told him, I said,

846
00:57:53,059 --> 00:57:57,294
"Hey, homes, this is just
another week for you."

847
00:57:57,296 --> 00:58:01,098
I think he knew that "This
is gonna make or break me."

848
00:58:02,968 --> 00:58:07,171
He knew that in order for him
to write his name in the book,

849
00:58:07,173 --> 00:58:10,140
he had to be exceptional.

850
00:58:10,142 --> 00:58:13,010
He was living a very comfortable life,

851
00:58:13,012 --> 00:58:15,946
but he wanted to live an exceptional life,

852
00:58:17,583 --> 00:58:21,218
and this was his exceptional feat.

853
00:58:30,596 --> 00:58:33,497
I remember just about
every play in that game.

854
00:58:33,499 --> 00:58:34,832
Every time Simpson got the ball,

855
00:58:34,834 --> 00:58:38,035
everyone was rushing to their,
uh, notepad to write it down.

856
00:58:38,037 --> 00:58:41,705
And the announcers kept counting it down.

857
00:58:41,707 --> 00:58:45,008
Well, gentlemen, we are coming
upon it, and, uh, The Juice should

858
00:58:45,010 --> 00:58:49,613
break the National Football League
rushing record in this next series.

859
00:58:49,615 --> 00:58:53,417
Simpson running left, Simpson
breaking loose, and there it is!

860
00:58:53,419 --> 00:58:58,355
All right! All right!

861
00:58:58,357 --> 00:59:00,224
He needed four yards, he
got five and this crowd,

862
00:59:00,226 --> 00:59:04,962
his whole team is gathering
around and congratulating him,

863
00:59:04,964 --> 00:59:09,099
hitting him on the head, there
isn't a person sitting down.

864
00:59:09,101 --> 00:59:12,469
He got the 1,863 pretty early in the game.

865
00:59:12,471 --> 00:59:14,872
And they said, "Okay, now
we're going for the 2,000."

866
00:59:14,874 --> 00:59:18,308
And now it's for the 2,000, Floyd.

867
00:59:21,280 --> 00:59:23,714
More than 100 yards,
O.J., O.J. cuts inside,

868
00:59:23,716 --> 00:59:26,583
O.J. gets wide, this is on!

869
00:59:26,585 --> 00:59:31,221
Now a race he's at midfield and he's
inside Jets territory at the 43 yard line.

870
00:59:31,223 --> 00:59:35,726
100 yards. How many games did
he get to 100 yards? Eleven?

871
00:59:35,728 --> 00:59:37,461
Once he got over 100 yards,

872
00:59:37,463 --> 00:59:39,329
a different excitement
started to hit the game.

873
00:59:39,331 --> 00:59:42,666
Well, he might do this. He
might actually hit 2,000.

874
00:59:42,668 --> 00:59:47,104
You had Jets fans who were
basically rooting for O.J.

875
00:59:47,106 --> 00:59:50,007
because they wanted to be part
of history, and I think, you know,

876
00:59:50,009 --> 00:59:52,676
I was basically a little kid,
but I think I felt that way.

877
00:59:52,678 --> 00:59:53,577
Who cared if The Jets won?

878
00:59:53,579 --> 00:59:55,078
Everybody loved O.J.

879
01:00:00,286 --> 01:00:05,155
O.J., he's got five yards,
and O.J. running left,

880
01:00:05,157 --> 01:00:08,525
O.J. five more. Maybe more. I don't know.

881
01:00:08,527 --> 01:00:14,198
They did it. They did it. Yeah!

882
01:00:15,968 --> 01:00:20,070
And when he did it, he was on my shoulder.

883
01:00:22,141 --> 01:00:28,846
I knew how important it was.
I contributed to that also.

884
01:00:28,848 --> 01:00:32,182
The defense has to give
the ball to the offense.

885
01:00:32,184 --> 01:00:35,385
I felt it. It was mine, too.

886
01:00:38,691 --> 01:00:42,226
Right after the game, there's
"Gotta get O.J. to the interview,"

887
01:00:42,228 --> 01:00:45,229
and he said, "I'm not coming in
unless you bring in all the guys."

888
01:00:45,231 --> 01:00:48,699
And we were in a tiny room. We
could barely fit in that room.

889
01:00:48,701 --> 01:00:52,202
He brought in all the offense. He
refused to go in that room without us.

890
01:00:52,204 --> 01:00:55,138
O.J., you brought 'em all with you.

891
01:00:55,140 --> 01:00:57,074
Yeah. Hey, they did the job, all of you.

892
01:00:57,076 --> 01:00:58,175
I want you to meet the boys. Here.

893
01:00:58,177 --> 01:01:01,078
Mike Montler, our... our... our center.

894
01:01:01,080 --> 01:01:03,780
Jim Braxton, Bob Penchion, Joe Ferguson.

895
01:01:03,782 --> 01:01:05,682
Didn't throw many passes this year,
but ball-handling is the thing.

896
01:01:07,152 --> 01:01:10,554
Donnie Green, Bobby
Chandler, Paul Seymour,

897
01:01:10,556 --> 01:01:12,256
Dave Foley, a former Jet.

898
01:01:13,425 --> 01:01:14,858
All right, all right!

899
01:01:14,860 --> 01:01:17,427
This is a guy, through the long winter

900
01:01:17,429 --> 01:01:19,062
wasn't supposed to play
any football this year.

901
01:01:19,064 --> 01:01:20,998
He had a heart problem, but you
came back, and you see what we did.

902
01:01:21,000 --> 01:01:24,334
JD Hill, "Crackback" Hill,
my main man Reg McKenzie.

903
01:01:24,336 --> 01:01:27,004
He was the most generous
guy you'd ever meet.

904
01:01:29,008 --> 01:01:31,675
When we broke the record, he
bought us a gold wristband.

905
01:01:31,677 --> 01:01:35,679
And on the back of it is,
"We did it. The Juice. 3088."

906
01:01:35,681 --> 01:01:38,749
He didn't say "2003", he said "3088",

907
01:01:38,751 --> 01:01:40,918
because that's how much the team rushed.

908
01:01:40,920 --> 01:01:43,787
I hope to stay in the, uh, league
long enough for, uh, you know,

909
01:01:43,789 --> 01:01:46,056
'til all these guys
get old so no young back

910
01:01:46,058 --> 01:01:48,158
can get behind 'em and break my record.

911
01:01:49,929 --> 01:01:53,330
'73 was like a rebirth of his celebrity.

912
01:01:58,137 --> 01:02:00,103
I was 22 years old, I thought, you know,

913
01:02:00,105 --> 01:02:03,206
"This is like being on
a team with Babe Ruth."

914
01:02:03,208 --> 01:02:07,210
Mentally, I think he was
ahead of, uh, a lot of people.

915
01:02:07,212 --> 01:02:12,382
From watching how he handled
himself, how he operated,

916
01:02:12,384 --> 01:02:17,688
my whole demeanor changed.
I began to wanna be like O.J.

917
01:02:20,492 --> 01:02:26,463
He was Baryshnikov. When somebody
is that great at something,

918
01:02:28,767 --> 01:02:32,736
when we see those
people, they are special.

919
01:02:35,107 --> 01:02:39,076
They just can do stuff
that other people can't do.

920
01:02:44,683 --> 01:02:49,920
You expect it of yourself. You hear
the crowd, but you don't hear it.

921
01:02:49,922 --> 01:02:54,257
I mean, you know they're cheering,
but that's the way it should be.

922
01:02:54,259 --> 01:02:58,328
When I'm in the open, I'm running,
this is how it is supposed to be.

923
01:02:58,330 --> 01:03:02,366
This is correct. This is
the natural state of things.

924
01:03:02,368 --> 01:03:06,336
I know whenever I've done it,
my feelings have always been,

925
01:03:06,338 --> 01:03:08,872
uh, that's nothing.
